				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: When Hashtags Backfire</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-10-09T17:05:15+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">October 9, 2014 1:05 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">October 9, 2014 1:05 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/10/09/today-in-small-business-when-hashtags-backfire/" data-title="Today in Small Business: When Hashtags Backfire" data-description="Facebook has a new local mobile advertising play. J.C. Penney is in the midst of an e-commerce renaissance.">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>The Economy</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>ADP reports that the Northeast is the only region in the country to <a href="//www.marketwired.com/press-release/adp-regional-employment-report-northeast-only-region-show-decrease-number-jobs-added-nyse-mco-1955742.htm">show a decrease in</a> the number of jobs added from August to September.</li>
<li>The 2014 <a href="//www.nbcnews.com/politics/first-read/2014-federal-budget-deficit-486-billion-lowest-2008-n221236">federal budget deficit</a> came in at $486 billion, its lowest level since 2008.</li>
<li>The United States has emerged as <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/08/business/energy-environment/reversing-the-flow-of-oil-.html">a major world exporter of oil</a>.</li>
</ul>
